/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nageeye is the second-oldest male runner to win New York City after 36-year-old Kenyan Paul Tergat in 2005 and the oldest man to win his first World Marathon Major since the series began in 2006.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999984186161, \"rank\": 1.5668913067137795e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Tergat\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Tergat\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Tergat\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Tergat\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chebet won New York City in 2022, sandwiched between two Boston Marathon titles.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999984186161, \"rank\": 1.5668913067137795e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7362846712492835e-15, \"text\": \"Boston Marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston_Marathon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conner Mantz, who was sixth, was the top American man, just as he was at the Olympic Trials in February and the Paris Games in August.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http