]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, no male or female runner won multiple World Marathon Majors for the first time since 2012 (including the Olympics and biennial world championships), excluding 2020.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men's marathoning appears to be entering a new era after nearly a decade of dominance from Kenyan Eliud Kipchoge, who turns 40 on Tuesday and failed to finish his most recent marathon at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's marathoning still has leading stars: Kenyan Ruth Chepngetich shattered the world record to win the Chicago Marathon in 2:09:56 on Oct. 13.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2655, \"end\": 2659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"score\": 0.6295676681341569, \"rank\": 0.5883916065283568, \"text\": \"Ruth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutchwoman Sifan Hassan won her first two marathon starts in 2023, then broke the Olympic record in Paris.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2761, \"end\": 2773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}, {\"begin\": 2850, \"end\": 2855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999721267162, \"rank\": 2.7873227513